LAGOS  – The Ausso Leadership Academy (ALA), one of the leading centres for the training of entrepreneurs in the country, is marking its fourth anniversary this week. The academy started with the launch of “The Entrepreneurs’ Hub” in Lagos in April 2018 Mr. Austin Okere, the Founder of CWG Plc, established the leadership academy. According to him, the academy offers a mentorship progranmme that prepares high performing intrapreneurs and entrepreneurs to lead and scale companies, organisations and institutions. “We help you to build a leadership bench strength that inculcates a culture of performance, accountability, pace and agility,” he stated Okere, who has an MBA from IESE Business School and over 30 years of industry experience, is an Entrepreneur-in-Residence at Columbia Business School, New York. He was appointed to the Advisory Board of the Global Business School Network in Washington DC in recognition of his major contribution to the development of business education and knowledge transfer in Africa. He was recognised with a Lifetime Entrepreneurship Achievement Award by the American University of Nigeria in 2017 for his dedicated service and outstanding entrepreneurial accomplishments and received the Nigerian Computer Society Special Presidential Award in 2016 and was named ICT Personality of the year by the society in 2014. POLL He was also named ICT Man of the Decade by ICT Watch – Africa Digital Network in 2012 and was listed on the United Kingdom’s C.Hub Magazine 100 Most Influential Creatives in 2016. Okere used the opportunity of the anniversary to appreciate God and the support from his Sola Okere, his wife, partners, customers, champions, and faculty for their confidence in him.